┃ loltty – psychedelic effects for your terminal ┃
┗━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━┛

‣‣‣ ALPHA VERSION (rapid prototype), will be rewritten later!

┌───────┐
│ What? │
└───────┘

Eventually:
An interactive cowsay, figlet, lolcat, matrix, rev, and more… all rolled into one.

Currently:
A proof-of-concept non-interactive lolcat reimplementation.
Soon to be more.

┌──────┐
│ Why? │
└──────┘

Because.

┌──────┐
│ How? │
└──────┘

Run it like this:

$ loltty [command [options] [arguments]]

So, for example…

• spawn a new shell:
  $ loltty

• run a rather psychedelic vim:
  $ loltty vim


The proof-of-concept works just like cat(1), that is:

$ lolcat [-p spread] [file ...]

It requires Unicode input, does not deal with combining characters,
and the presence of ANSI codes in the input lets it choke exactly
like lolcat does. The spread must be an integer value (default: 8).

